 "incline_code": "Vertical",
 "intro_html": "Durance Route on the Devils Tower in Wyoming is listed as one of the 50 classic climbs in North America. It's a 4-6 pitch route in which the harder sections are mainly off-width and hand-cracks with a few spots of chimney. Don't forget to register at the Visitor's Center before the climb or you risk a fine. This is a crowded route so get on super early or be ready to follow others and possibly do the abseil descent in the dark with headtorches.",
